{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:55:56.909Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM APIs structure conversation as an ordered list of messages, each with a role that tells the model how to interpret the content. System, user, and assistant roles form the backbone of agent prompts; tool and function roles carry structured results back into the context. Correct role assignment prevents the model from confusing instructions with user input or hallucinating prior assistant actions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A role tag (system, user, assistant, tool, or legacy function) paired with content—plain text, multipart blocks, or structured tool payloads. The model is trained to condition on these prefixes so system rules persist across turns and tool outputs are distinguishable from natural dialogue."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mis-typed roles break agent safety boundaries (user content treated as system policy) and tool loops (results not recognized). Frameworks map runtime events to roles: user query → user, model plan → assistant, API result → tool."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Clear separation",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — policy vs input vs model output vs environment feedback"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tool loop support",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — standardized tool_call_id linking"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Provider portability",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — same conceptual roles across OpenAI and Anthropic"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Role semantics are convention + training—not enforced by JSON schema alone"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Some models ignore or overweight system messages depending on tuning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Anthropic uses top-level system string; OpenAI uses system role message—adapters must translate"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Typical agent message stack"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "system:     global agent policy, tool rules, output format\nuser:       end-user or orchestrator instruction\nassistant:  prior model outputs (may include tool_calls)\ntool:       JSON result from executed tool (linked by tool_call_id)\nuser:       next user turn..."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OpenAI tool loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "messages = [\n    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"Use tools when needed. Reply in JSON when asked.\"},\n    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What is the weather in Tokyo?\"},\n]\n\n# First completion — model may return tool_calls on the assistant message\nresp = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    messages=messages,\n    tools=[{\n        \"type\": \"function\",\n        \"function\": {\n            \"name\": \"get_weather\",\n            \"parameters\": {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\"city\": {\"type\": \"string\"}},\n                \"required\": [\"city\"],\n            },\n        },\n    }],\n)\n\nassistant_msg = resp.choices[0].message\nmessages.append(assistant_msg.model_dump(exclude_none=True))\n\nif assistant_msg.tool_calls:\n    call = assistant_msg.tool_calls[0]\n    messages.append({\n        \"role\": \"tool\",\n        \"tool_call_id\": call.id,\n        \"content\": '{\"temp_c\": 22, \"condition\": \"clear\"}',\n    })\n    follow = client.chat.completions.create(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", messages=messages)\n    print(follow.choices[0].message.content)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic system + user/assistant"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "response = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n    max_tokens=512,\n    system=\"You only answer using provided tool results.\",\n    messages=[\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Book a meeting tomorrow 9am.\"},\n        {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"I will check calendar availability.\"},\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Calendar says: slot free at 9am.\"},\n    ],\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Always assign roles explicitly in hand-built prompts. When using chat templates in local inference (llama.cpp, vLLM), ensure the template emits the same role tokens the model was trained on."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Putting user-controlled text in system role to \"force\" behavior—prompt injection risk"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assistant role for tool JSON that should be tool role"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Duplicate or out-of-order tool_call_id references"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Concatenating multiple users into one message without clear delimiters"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep system prompts stable; put volatile data in user or tool messages"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Truncate history by role-aware rules (drop old tool blobs first)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document role mapping in your agent framework for contributors"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mental model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Roles are lane markers on a highway: system sets the rules, user asks, assistant responds, tool reports ground truth from the environment."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "system / user / assistant / tool each carry distinct semantics"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tool loops require assistant tool_calls + matching tool messages"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Provider APIs differ in system placement—use adapter layers"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Never treat untrusted input as system-level policy"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
